{{en-verb|tells|telling|told}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[count]], [[reckon]], or [[enumerate]].
#: {{ux|en|All '''told''', there were over a dozen.&emsp; Can you '''tell''' time on a clock?&emsp; He had '''untold''' wealth.}}
#* '''1590''', {{w|Edmund Spenser}}, ''{{w|The Faerie Queene}}'', II.vii:
#*: And in his lap a masse of coyne he '''told''', / And turned vpsidowne, to feede his eye / A couetous desire with his huge threasury.
